sentences: René Thomas (25 February 1927 – 3 January 1975) was a Belgian jazz guitarist.
In the early 1950s, he moved to Paris, France, and became part of the modern jazz scene, playing in the style of Jimmy Raney.
He spent brief periods in the United States from 1958 to 1962.
Thomas died of a heart attack in Santander, Spain, at the age of 47 on 3 January 1975.
